{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, only entities with the corresponding hash can access and retrieve the IPFS hash and the associated explanation, ensuring controlled access even in a distributed network.",
    "Lastly, the regulator's role is responsible for auditing and has access to the explanations to predict the user at fault using audit trails if system failure were to occur.",
    "Non-AI Threats and DefensesReferring to Figure 3, we specifically focus on DDoS attacks and supply chain issues.",
    "Even though these attacks are common problems, we consider threats relevant to BC4LLMs.",
    "Ibrahim et al. [48] suggest using a public blockchain to prevent DDoS attacks on IoT devices."
  ]
